body:
This adds `useQueryRule` to our Hooks collection. Similarly to the current API, the example implements
- `QueryRuleContext`: which applies ruleContexts based on filters to trigger context dependent Rules.
- `QueryRuleCustomData`:  which displays custom data from Rules.

This hook is a bridge to `connectQueryRule`.

Example of a simple banner

```js
export function Banner(props) {
  const { items } = useQueryRules({
    genre: () => ['Comedy', 'Thriller'],
  });

  return <>
    items.map(item => <a href={item.link}>{item.title}</a>)
  </>
}

function App(props) {
  return (
    <InstantSearch {...props}>
      <Banner />

      {/* ... */}
    </InstantSearch>
  );
}
```

closes [FX-444](https://algolia.atlassian.net/browse/FX-444)
